  "body": "### Description\n\nWe use `quarkus-micrometer-registry-prometheus` and it took us a long (very long) while to realize we had an issue with some of our metrics, because we do not get the micrometer errors via its MeterRegistry.\r\n\r\nWe found out about our issue by adding a `onMeterRegistrationFailed` listener to the quarkus' `CompositeMeterRegistry`.\r\n\r\nTo add that listener we had to modify and injecter MeterRegistry in a startup bean so it can be done early enough.\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to have a way to tweak the `CompositeMeterRegistry` out of the box so we can modify it's configuration.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
